Here's someone just now fixing my kitchen floor. And I'm pretending right now that I still have a job and am working from home while I sit on Too Hot to Handle.
If I could damn well manage to open the file. (Fuck One Drive.)
*Sound of a hacker* I'm in.
And that's when he starts drilling really loudly. Hurrah.
It feels unpleasantly passive-aggressive to crank my air purifier all the way up, but I can smell the wood dust, so it would actually be completely okay even if he wasn't a mask opponent. And do I really need to protect myself?
I would really like to go back to bed, but I can't until he's gone.
At least I finally finished revising Chapter 4!
Chapter five is long, but so damn terrifying. Oh yeah, that's the good stuff!
I'm doing Find and Replace for … ➡️ ellipsis symbol and there are 54 in this chapter 😅
But no, I stick to my decision. Natural language is mostly fragmented, especially when you get emotional.
The craftsman is now using the vacuum cleaner. Hopefully, that means he'll be done soon.
He went out to cut something (at least, that's what it sounds like). I secretly checked how far he is. There's still a lot to do :(
7 more pages in Chapter 5. It's still my favorite chapter and it's pretty well organized – mostly changes to the text and very small corrections in dialogue, and I need to phrase everything a bit more concisely. But I could really use a break and a tea right now, but the guy is still in my kitchen.
Now he just started vacuuming dust again. Hopefully, that's a good sign.
The kitchen guy is gone!
He told me he had made a cost estimate for the entire floor, but the landlords were too cheap and only paid for the part next to the door that wasn't in order anymore. Feels so much better.
The house is being ventilated, and my air purifier is running in the kitchen while I drink tea in the garden!
